The paper discusses the application of artificial intelligence in the field of robotics, specifically in human-robot teaming. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. The paper also mentions the importance of maintaining a behavioral model of human teammates, which falls under the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The concept of plan explicability is also discussed, which relates to the Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC) sub-category. The paper also addresses the problem of human-robot cooperation, which falls under the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category. Finally, the paper compares the plans generated by their algorithm with plans created by humans, which suggests that the paper may also belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category.
